other_tests.findings: The appendix is visualized in the right lower quadrant, with hyperdense internal contents and no evidence of intraluminal gas. There is a small radiodensity contained within the appendix, possibly a small appendicolith. The overall caliber of the appendix is increased, measuring 10-11 mm in largest diameter. There is a trace amount of adjacent fat stranding and no evidence of free fluid or other appendiceal rupture.
